#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Security Settings with &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The &yast; module <guimenu>Security Center and Hardening</guimenu> offers a "
"central clearinghouse to configure security-related settings for "
"&productname;. Use it to configure security aspects such as settings for the "
"login procedure and for password creation, for boot permissions, user "
"creation or for default file permissions. Launch it from the &yast; control "
"center by <menuchoice> <guimenu>Security and Users</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Security Center and Hardening</guimenu> </menuchoice> . The "
"<guimenu>Security Center</guimenu> dialog always starts with the "
"<guimenu>Security Overview</guimenu> , and other configuration dialogues are "
"available from the right pane."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Security Overview</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>Security Overview</guimenu> displays a comprehensive list of "
"the most important security settings for your system. The security status of "
"each entry in the list is clearly visible. A green check mark indicates a "
"secure setting while a red cross indicates an entry as being insecure. Click "
"<guimenu>Help</guimenu> to open an overview of the setting and information "
"on how to make it secure. To change a setting, click the corresponding link "
"in the Status column. Depending on the setting, the following entries are "
"available:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Enabled</guimenu> / <guimenu>Disabled</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click this entry to toggle the status of the setting to either enabled or "
"disabled."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Configure</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click this entry to launch another &yast; module for configuration. You will "
"return to the Security Overview when leaving the module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Unknown</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A setting's status is set to unknown when the associated service is not "
"installed. Such a setting does not represent a potential security risk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "&yast; Security Center and Hardening: Security Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Predefined Security Configurations</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productname; comes with three <guimenu>Predefined Security Configurations</"
"guimenu> . These configurations affect all the settings available in the "
"<guimenu>Security Center</guimenu> module. Each configuration can be "
"modified to your needs using the dialogues available from the right pane "
"changing its state to <guimenu>Custom Settings</guimenu> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Workstation</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A configuration for a workstation with any kind of network connection "
"(including a connection to the Internet)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Roaming Device</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This setting is designed for a laptop or tablet that connects to different "
"networks."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Network Server</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Security settings designed for a machine providing network services such as "
"a Web server, file server, name server, etc. This set provides the most "
"secure configuration of the predefined settings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Custom Settings</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A pre-selected <guimenu>Custom Settings</guimenu> (when opening the "
"<guimenu>Predefined Security Configurations</guimenu> dialog) indicates that "
"one of the predefined sets has been modified. Actively choosing this option "
"does not change the current configuration&mdash;you will need to change it "
"using the <guimenu>Security Overview</guimenu> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Password Settings</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Passwords that are easy to guess are a major security issue. The "
"<guimenu>Password Settings</guimenu> dialog provides the means to ensure "
"that only secure passwords can be used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Check New Passwords</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By activating this option, a warning will be issued if new passwords appear "
"in a dictionary, or if they are proper names (proper nouns)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Minimum Acceptable Password Length</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the user chooses a password with a length shorter than specified here, a "
"warning will be issued."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Number of Passwords to Remember</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When password expiration is activated (via <guimenu>Password Age</"
"guimenu> ), this setting stores the given number of a user's previous "
"passwords, preventing their reuse."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Password Encryption Method</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose a password encryption algorithm. Normally there is no need to change "
"the default (Blowfish)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:217
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Password Age</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Activate password expiration by specifying a minimum and a maximum time "
"limit (in days). By setting the minimum age to a value greater than "
"<literal>0</literal> days, you can prevent users from immediately changing "
"their passwords again (and in doing so circumventing the password "
"expiration). Use the values <literal>0</literal> and <literal>99999</"
"literal> to deactivate password expiration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Days Before Password Expires Warning</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:234
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a password expires, the user receives a warning in advance. Specify the "
"number of days prior to the expiration date that the warning should be "
"issued."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Boot Settings</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure which users can shut down the machine via the graphical login "
"manager in this dialog. You can also specify how <keycombo> <keycap function="
"\"control\"/> <keycap function=\"alt\"/> <keycap function=\"delete\"/> </"
"keycombo> will be interpreted and who can hibernate the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:256
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Login Settings</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "This dialog lets you configure security-related login settings:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:264
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Delay after Incorrect Login Attempt</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:267
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To make it difficult to guess a user's password by repeatedly logging in, it "
"is recommended to delay the display of the login prompt that follows an "
"incorrect login. Specify the value in seconds. Make sure that users who have "
"mistyped their passwords do not need to wait too long."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Allow Remote Graphical Login</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:302
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When checked, the graphical login manager (GDM) can be accessed from the "
"network. This is a potential security risk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:311
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>User Addition</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Set minimum and maximum values for user and group IDs. These default "
"settings would rarely need to be changed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: security_yast2_security.xml:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Miscellaneous Settings</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Other security settings that do not fit the above-mentioned categories are "
"listed here:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:328
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>File Permissions</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productname; comes with three predefined sets of file permissions for "
"system files. These permission sets define whether a regular user may read "
"log files or start certain programs. <guimenu>Easy</guimenu> file "
"permissions are suitable for stand-alone machines. These settings allow "
"regular users to, for example, read most system files. See the file "
"<filename>/etc/permissions.easy</filename> for the complete configuration. "
"The <guimenu>Secure</guimenu> file permissions are designed for multiuser "
"machines with network access. A thorough explanation of these settings can "
"be found in <filename>/etc/permissions.secure</filename> . The "
"<guimenu>Paranoid</guimenu> settings are the most restrictive ones and "
"should be used with care. See <filename>/etc/permissions.paranoid</filename> "
"for more information."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:349
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>User Launching updatedb</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:352
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The program <command>updatedb</command> scans the system and creates a "
"database of all file locations which can be queried with the command "
"<command>locate</command> . When <command>updatedb</command> is run as user "
"nobody, only world-readable files will be added to the database. When run as "
"user &rootuser;, almost all files (except the ones root is not allowed to "
"read) will be added."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_yast2_security.xml:386
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Enable Magic SysRq Keys</guimenu>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_yast2_security.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The magic SysRq key is a key combination that enables you to have some "
"control over the system even when it has crashed. The complete documentation "
"can be found at <link xlink:href=\"https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/"
"admin-guide/sysrq.html\"/> ."
msgstr ""
